# Sample HTTP requests for local testing
# Run these using VS Code REST Client or with curl/httpie from terminal.

### Health check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Demo login (creates a demo user and returns access token)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/demo-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "project_manager"
}

# Example curl commands:
# curl http://localhost:5000/health
# curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/demo-login -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"role":"project_manager"}'

# If you get an access token from demo-login, use it in subsequent requests:
# GET http://localhost:5000/api/users
# Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN>
